---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { breadcrumbSchema } from "../lib/seo";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn who maintains AI Soc Corpus, how NUS AI Society reviews corpus topics, and how the knowledge base supports AI learners."
  canonicalPath="/about/"
  jsonLd={breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: "Home", path: "/" },
    { name: "About", path: "/about/" },
  ])}
>
  <section class="about-page">
    <h1>About AI Soc Corpus</h1>
    <p>
      AI Soc Corpus is an interconnected artificial intelligence and machine
      learning knowledge base maintained for NUS AI Society members and
      beginners. It turns individual concepts into a navigable learning graph,
      so readers can move between prerequisites, related ideas, citations, and
      topic explanations without losing context.
    </p>

    <h2>Maintainers</h2>
    <p>
      The corpus is maintained by contributors connected to NUS AI Society.
      Topic pages are authored through GitHub pull requests, checked with local
      validation scripts, and reviewed for clarity, mathematical correctness,
      citations, and internal links before they become part of the public
      corpus.
    </p>

    <h2>Editorial Standard</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Every corpus topic must include validated frontmatter metadata.</li>
      <li>Explanations should be beginner-aware without sacrificing rigor.</li>
      <li>LaTeX, citations, and wiki links are checked before publication.</li>
      <li>Topics should connect to prerequisites and related concepts.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For contributions, use the GitHub workflow described on the contribution
      page. For society contact, email
      <a href="mailto:outreach@nusaisociety.org">outreach@nusaisociety.org</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about-page h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-page h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .about-page p,
  .about-page li {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .about-page ul {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  .about-page a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }
</style>
